            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;If you&apos;re using Python 3.7 you must be a time traveler from 2018. If you refer to 2021, provide a test with Python 3.9. &lt;code&gt;PyThreadState_SetAsyncExc&lt;/code&gt; method just does a &quot;schedule&quot; for an thread exit. It does &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; kill a thread especially if it&apos;s executing external C-libraries. Try to kill a &lt;code&gt;sleep(100)&lt;/code&gt; with your method. It will be &quot;killed&quot; after 100 seconds. It&apos;s just as effective as the &lt;code&gt;while flag:&lt;/code&gt; -&amp;gt; &lt;code&gt;flag = False&lt;/code&gt; method.&lt;/span&gt;

